### **Successful FPIC Implementations — Real-World Wins (Plain English)**

**FPIC = Free, Prior, Informed Consent**  
→ When done right, it builds trust, shares benefits, and prevents harm. Here are **5 strong examples** where FPIC worked — with results.

---

### **1. Innu Nation & Voisey's Bay Mine (Canada, 2002)**

| **What Happened** | **How FPIC Worked** |
|-------------------|---------------------|
| A mining company wanted to build a **nickel mine** in Labrador. | - **Free & Prior**: Early talks with Innu leaders (no rush). <br> - **Informed**: Full details on jobs, environment, and money. <br> - **Consent**: Innu said **YES** after 2 years of meetings. |
| **Result** | Innu got 7% ownership, $2B in benefits, and training jobs. Mine runs smoothly for 20+ years. No protests. |

> *“We’re partners now, not just neighbors.”* – Innu leader

---

### **2. Baram Dam Cancellation (Malaysia, 2015)**

| **What Happened** | **How FPIC Worked** |
|-------------------|---------------------|
| Government planned a **hydro dam** that would flood Penan and Kenyah villages. | - **Free**: No threats — open community votes. <br> - **Prior**: Consulted 2 years before surveys. <br> - **Informed**: Showed maps, flood risks, and alternatives. <br> - **Consent**: Tribes said **NO** — government listened. |
| **Result** | Dam canceled. Land protected. Tribes keep their forests and way of life. |

---

### **3. REDD+ Forest Projects (Vietnam, 2010–2015)**

| **What Happened** | **How FPIC Worked** |
|-------------------|---------------------|
| UN program paid villages to **protect forests** instead of cutting them. | - **Free**: Village elders led talks. <br> - **Prior**: Started with local leaders months early. <br> - **Informed**: Explained carbon credits and money sharing. <br> - **Consent**: 90% of villages said **YES** after training. |
| **Result** | 3 pilot sites saved 10,000+ hectares. Villages earned $50K/year. No land fights. UN called it a **model**. |

---

### **4. Maasai Mara Conservation (Kenya, 2000s)**

| **What Happened** | **How FPIC Worked** |
|-------------------|---------------------|
| Tourists wanted to visit **Maasai lands** for wildlife safaris. | - **Free**: Maasai decided as a group. <br> - **Prior**: Planned 1 year ahead. <br> - **Informed**: Showed how tourism money would build schools/clinics. <br> - **Consent**: Maasai said **YES** with rules (no fences, share profits). |
| **Result** | Maasai earn $1M/year from fees. Wildlife protected. Schools built. Tourism and culture thrive together. |

---

### **5. Sami Wind Farm (Norway, 2010s)**

| **What Happened** | **How FPIC Worked** |
|-------------------|---------------------|
| A wind farm was planned on **Sami reindeer lands**. | - **Free**: Sami Parliament voted openly. <br> - **Prior**: Consulted 3 years before building. <br> - **Informed**: Explained noise/wind impacts on herding. <br> - **Consent**: Sami said **YES** after changes (fewer turbines, reindeer paths). |
| **Result** | Farm built with Sami co-ownership. Clean energy + $500K/year for herders. No migration disruptions. |

---

### **What Makes FPIC Work Here?**

| **Success Tip** | **Why It Matters** |
|-----------------|-------------------|
| **Start Early** | Time for real talks, not rushed yeses |
| **Share Power** | Indigenous leaders run meetings |
| **Real Benefits** | Jobs, money, or land rights — not empty promises |
| **Follow Through** | Write agreements, check yearly |

---

### **FPT Makes It Easier**

In FPT, FPIC is **built-in code**:
- **App votes** for tribes (secure, private).
- **Auto-logs** every talk (can't erase).
- **Alerts** if rules break.
- **Space version**: For satellites using star knowledge.

---

### **One Sentence**

> **Successful FPIC = Early honest talks that lead to real wins for everyone — and stick to the deal.**

---

**These stories show**:  
FPIC isn't a hassle — it's a **win-win**.  
Tribes thrive, projects succeed.

